column5: beast
Hopefully it wasn't a 620 or 621VS.
sweet ride congrats
Very nice rig!!! Now go get it all slimy and smelly!!

Great rig!! How you compare it with Lund Tyee 1950 or Baron? I guess it's more likely a tournamnet-related boat, and Tyuee or Baron is more likely Salmon and mult-species boat (deeper and wider), right? They are all for great water.

To be honest...I have no idea as this is my first Lund (and first non-bass boat). Yes, the boat is a tournament series boat.  I was out on Quinte last Thursday, in 5 footers, and it handled them with ease!
Better still go a little further east and slime her up with some real fish, that eat 8lb walleyes for snacks
Is that an offer to take me out?! lol  Are there fish that will eat 13.6 lber's too? Cause we landed one of those today!

Hey everyone,  Since this year has been pretty bad so far...I thought I would share something GOOD that happened! lol  I sold my 2006 Ranger, and picked up:  2006 Lund Pro-V (2025) Mangnum IFS 225 HP Mercury Optimax 9.9 HP Mercury Pro Kicker 101 lbs thrust, Minn Kota Terrova with auto-pilot   I opted for a deeper boat, as I have been slowly migrating from Bass fishing, into Walleye fishing/guiding.  I have since got the boat wrapped in our company's brand (G2 Angling).  Enjoy, I know I sure am!
I'm totally jellin!
Killer rig man, perfect for those Quinte Eyes. Deep V's are waaaayy more versitile than Bass boats. She'll handle nice out there.
Sweet boat, Jamie!  Enjoy!
dang that is pretty much what I want in my next boat..2.5 years away    I really want a merc verado on it ..but I would take that one too

Thanks everyone!  If you see me out on the Bay of Quinte, be sure to come say hi!
